English Version

Post-Doc position in the domain of « Cooperative Crisis Management »

Context and Mission Statement: The Applicant will work within the context of funded R&D projects dedicated to crisis management support in the area of large scale or serious damages industrial troubles, involving several different organisations

Key Words: crisis, NRBCE, resilience, persons-machines cooperation, complex systems, big data analysis, knowledge engineering, high reliability organizations

Requirements: The Applicant will have a PhD in Computer Science and should have knowledge and experience with modeling and prototyping. An interest in environmental and organizational problems is desirable, as well as a culture in sociology.

Laboratory: The Applicant will be member of the CReSTIC laboratory, linked to the Université Reims Champagne Ardenne, and will cooperate with other labs in Paris or Troyes.

Location: Paris, Reims or Troyes

Duration: 6 months

Hiring date: December 2013

Remuneration: around 2500 € per month

Requested documents: To apply, please send a cover letter, a detailed Curriculum Vitae with a list of publications, a short description of your current research interests, and names/email of two different researchers who know your research capacities to:

Francis Rousseaux, francis.rousseaux@univ-reims.fr (+33 (0)6 78 26 77 40)
